==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Serving
<hw>Serv"ing</hw>, <def><pos>a. & n.</pos> from
<er>Serve</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Serving board</b></col> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>, <cd>a flat
piece of wood used in serving ropes.</cd> -- <col><b>Serving
maid</b></col>, <cd>a female servant; a maidservant.</cd> --
<col><b>Serving mallet</b></col> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>, <cd>a wooden
instrument shaped like a mallet, used in serving ropes.</cd> --
<col><b>Serving man</b></col>, <cd>a male servant, or attendant; a
manservant.</cd> -- <col><b>Serving stuff</b></col> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>,
<cd>small lines for serving ropes.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Servite</ent>⟦br⟧
